## 9. Limitation of Liability

IN NO EVENT WILL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDERS OR CONTRIBUTORS (INCLUDING PARDUS) BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS LICENSE OR THE USE OR DISTRIBUTION OF THE LICENSED WORK, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

---

## 10. Termination

Your rights under this License will terminate automatically if You fail to comply with any of its terms and do not cure such breach within thirty (30) days after becoming aware of it. Upon termination, You must cease all distribution of the Licensed Work and Derivative Works.

---

## 11. Future Versions

Pardus may publish revised versions of this License. You may choose to follow the terms of the version under which the Licensed Work was received, or to comply with any later version explicitly published by Pardus.

